# UI & Components

Follow `docs/website-design.md` for visual tone.

## One design system

- **Single component home**: `apps/website/src/components/ui/` for primitives; `components/` for composed features
- **No duplicate components** — one `Button`, one `Input`, one `Badge`; extend via props, not `ButtonPrimary` / `Button2`
- **Design tokens in one file**: `styles/tokens.css` or Tailwind theme extension — no hardcoded hex scattered in components

## Styling rules

- Minimal palette, high-contrast typography, generous whitespace (marketing/solo)
- Borders over shadows; radius 12–20px; no glassmorphism or decorative animation
- Admin (`/admin/*`) may be denser; same tokens and primitives as marketing

## Route surfaces

| Route | UX |
|---|---|
| `/` | Content-first marketing |
| `/solo/*` | One task per screen; large tap targets |
| `/admin/*` | Functional tables, status badges, detail drawer |

## Component checklist (before adding new)

1. Does a primitive already exist in `components/ui`?
2. Can an existing component take a `variant` prop instead?
3. Is this logic-only? Use a hook in `hooks/` — not a wrapper component

## Avoid

- Feature-card grids on marketing unless content-driven
- Dispatch controls on web (campaign editor, load board)
- Inline styles except truly one-off layout tweaks
